!!Etymology
From Javanese `ꦒꦫꦸꦣ` (//garudha//, “eagle”), from Sanskrit `गरुड` (//garuḍa//)

# A large mythical bird or bird-like creature that appears in both Hindu and Buddhist mythology. //Garuda// is the son of //Kadruva//. The bird is represented as an eagle, especially as //elang Jawa// or Javan hawk-eagle
